Author: cevr <seeve.c@gmail.com>
Date:   Wed Jun 17 13:54:33 2026 -0400

    feat(cms)(per-page-content): Content.getPage + getForm multi-object read path

    Add the per-object read path (ADR 0008, settled #7): `Content.getPage` and
    `getForm` each read their own bucket object (`content/pages/<page>.json`,
    `forms/<form>.json`) through the registry schema's own decode boundary, fall back
    to the bundled default on every failure mode, and cache independently via one
    `Effect.cachedInvalidateWithTTL` per object. A corrupt page object falls back to
    its default and cannot poison another object's decode (ADR 0008's headline
    blast-radius property).

    Parameterize `bust` over a closed `BustTarget` (`bustSite` / `bustPage(id)` /
    `bustForm(id)`) so publishing one object invalidates ONLY that object's read
    cache. `DraftEditor.publish` maps its `ContentScope` to the target via
    `bustTargetOf`, so a page publish busts only that page — never another page,
    form, or the conference (`site`) cache. `BustTarget` is defined in
    content.server over the registry ids (not DraftEditor's ContentScope) to keep the
    read path free of the draft/published key pair and avoid an import cycle.

    Tests: getPage/getForm fallback-to-default; reading a real published object;
    per-object cache-bust isolation (busting About leaves FAQ/form/conference
    cached); one malformed page object falls back without breaking another.

